- `homF g ≫ homF f : Hom (Hom Z c) (Hom X c)` is `fun h => f ≫ (g ≫ h)`.

But `(f ≫ g) ≫ h = f ≫ (g ≫ h)` by associativity of composition, so `homF (f ≫ g) = homF g ≫ homF f`.

